(1, 'school-buses.jpg', 'It was a normal school day for Mary E Bryant Elementary School in Tampa, Florida. The school day ended and children were going back home. Unfortunately, one of the school buses was in for a disaster.', 'school-bus-falls-into-pond', 'Normal Day In Florida', 7, '9f45346d8f439f4bd867f87a9747d684'),
(2, 'school-bus-driver.jpg', 'While driving, the bus encountered a problem. The brakes ceased from functioning and the bus driver lost control. The driver needed to move the bus somewhere safer away from other cars.', 'school-bus-falls-into-pond', 'A Recipe For Disaster', 6, 'f196d60f0f7a06cb94d6ac68420e2b35'),
(3, 'alligator.jpg', 'The driver tried to maneuver the vehicle, but couldn&#039;t. Despite all his efforts, the bus was headed straight towards the lake.', 'school-bus-falls-into-pond', 'Destination: Lake', 5, 'aeb2e9ee16b4595999d5331ca876daff'),
(4, 'school-bus-in-pond.jpg', 'The bad news was that it wasn&#039;t just a lake. It was an alligator pond! The bus rolled and stopped in the shallow pond. Even when it wasn&#039;t that deep, the pond engulfed half of the bus.', 'school-bus-falls-into-pond', 'Stuck With The Gators', 4, '629da21a3ac4d059349544ce17deeac6'),
(5, 'police-line.jpg', 'Parents and authorities were notified of the situation. Their mission now was to bring 27 kids to safety.', 'school-bus-falls-into-pond', 'Search and Rescue', 3, '1a0de524fd52f13f35b2da10d7c3699e'),
(6, 'school-bus-tipped-over.jpg', 'Nicolas Sierra, a 10 year old boy that is a member of the school&#039;s safety patrol is now considered a hero. Why? He rescued three kindergartners who were trapped inside the bus. Nicolas is a shy boy, but during the situation he boosted up his guts and went to save!', 'school-bus-falls-into-pond', 'The Miracle Boy', 2, '9ce0151d7bff47dd6761a2c0f524f8c8'),
(7, 'honoring-boy.jpg', 'Surprisingly, nobody got injured in this peculiar incident. The cause of the accident and why the brakes stopped are still being investigated. On the other hand, Nicolas got recognized as a hero.', 'school-bus-falls-into-pond', 'No Fatalities', 1, '1700c56a2e83f78c95ac6bb50fe1c7fc'),
(8, '', '<p>College is expensive so you want to get a degree that pays for the expenses. Finding the best degree to get has its flaws though; you might find yourself with money, but not satisfied with your job.</p>\r\n<p>Ultimately, you do have to stop and think before you declare your major. We&rsquo;ve researched these degrees and compiled a list from bottom to top to show you the different college degrees that pay.</p>\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #333333;">6. Nutrition</span></h1>\r\n<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><em><img src="../../stories/media/images/fruits-1598767_960_720 (1).jpg" alt="http://whateven.com/stories/media/images/fruits-1598767_960_720 (1).jpg" width="960" height="540" border="0" /></em></span></p>\r\n<p>Love food and good nutrition? Well, nutritionists surround themselves with just that. They advise and tell people what to eat and what not to eat. It seems easy and not that much of a struggle right? Well once you get your nutritional degree you can start making $55,000/year. Not bad. The growth of this industry is at 21% and you don&rsquo;t even have to rely on a career to pay your bills, that&rsquo;s because you can open your own nutritional clinic.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s not the highest paying degree out there, but it could be the easiest college degree you could get with that kind of salary. Most engineering jobs start off at just barely $55,000, and the amount of work you have to put into Calculus doesn&rsquo;t seem worth it. This is why we are ranking this degree at number 10 of the highest paying bachelor degree.</p>\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #333333;">5. Computer Engineering</span></h1>\r\n<p><img src="../../stories/media/images/computer-engineering.jpg" width="650" height="432" border="0" /></p>\r\n<p>Now to start off our real list. Computer engineering is a degree and idea of creating computer hardware and chips for them to function in machines. They use some programmatic skills and mostly circuitry to build useful computer parts. It sounds difficult and that&rsquo;s because it is. We wouldn&rsquo;t recommend this degree to anyone not interested in circuitry and computer architecture.<br />[GOOGLE]<br />The starting salary for a computer engineer looking for a job is at $66,000. The in-class struggles seem to be worth it at the end based on the pay. Making computer engineering one of the best bachelor degrees to get!</p>\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #333333;">4. Finance</span><span style="color: #800000;"><em><br /></em></span></h1>\r\n<p><img src="../../stories/media/images/finance-degree.jpg" alt="finance degree" width="624" height="391" border="0" /></p>\r\n<p>How does this rank better than computer engineering you may ask? Well, in order to be a budget analyst that&rsquo;s what degree you need. It seems like not a high paying degree, but the world is all about supply and demand.</p>\r\n<p>Budget analysts typically make $69,000/year and the effort put into such a degree is not bad.</p>\r\n<p>So what do budget analysts do? They typically organize the finances of private and public institutions. Sounds fun dealing with money right? That&rsquo;s really what you&rsquo;ve been studying in school the whole time!</p>\r\n<p>As we progress deeper in this list, you&rsquo;ll see that the degree doesn&rsquo;t need to be high paying in order for you to get a high paying job.</p>\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #333333;">3. Mining Engineering</span></h1>\r\n<p><img src="../../stories/media/images/mining-engineering.jpg" alt="mining engineer" width="650" height="379" border="0" /></p>\r\n<p>Mining engineers extract minerals from the Earth using various technologies. They have to have some sort of understanding on how to obtain Earth minerals without damage being resulted. A student typically studying for a mining engineering degree must go through rigorous forms of mathematics and chemistry. After that, 79% of people who work with their mining engineering degrees find that their job changes the world.<br /><br />So if you want a degree that makes you happy in the long run, here&rsquo;s one for you. The average starting salary is $71,000. Which makes it one of the best college degrees to get!</p>\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #333333;">2. Computer Science</span></h1>\r\n<p><img src="../../stories/media/images/computer-science-degree.jpg" alt="computer science" width="650" height="433" border="0" /></p>\r\n<p>There is a very high demand of computer scientists around the world. From their app making, to their website building. Computer scientists are needed greatly because their supply is so low. Even though computer engineering is a bit more circuitry, computer science only tops it because of the low supply of workers. With a salary of $74,000 a year, it&rsquo;s no wonder getting a degree in computer science pays off greatly!</p>\r\n<p><br />The beauty of this degree is not just in the secure job placement once you graduate, but in how easily you can become a freelancer. While you have a full time job, you can actually work on projects on the side. You can build websites/apps for people and get paid for it. Two incomes easily at your hands.</p>\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #333333;">1. Petroleum Engineering</span></h1>\r\n<p><img src="../../stories/media/images/petroleum-engineering.JPG" width="650" height="393" border="0" /></p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s all about oil. Your car, your lawn mower and even the plastics that you use. With this degree, you can land a job as a petroleum engineer. What do they do you may ask? Well, they&rsquo;re involved in almost all the stages of oil production.<br /><br />There are many top paying college degrees, but this one is very unique. The need for oil is increasing and won&rsquo;t go away anytime soon, so big oil companies are paying big money to get people stationed and ready for the black gold production. A petroleum engineer can be paid as much as $101,000 to $168,000 per year.</p>', 'highest-paying-degrees', '', 1, ''),
(227, '', '<p><img src="../../stories/media/images/wendys.jpg" alt="Wendy''s" width="1280" height="720" /></p>\r\n<p>Its been 4 days since the new year started and already there''s something brewing on Twitter. It all started on Wednesday when burger joint Wendy''s Tweeted the following Tweet out a week ago:</p>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">Our beef is way too cool to ever be frozen. ðŸ˜Ž <a href="https://t.co/QuXECJtlq5">pic.twitter.com/QuXECJtlq5</a></p>\r\n&mdash; Wendy''s (@Wendys) <a href="https://twitter.com/Wendys/status/814975590474207232">December 30, 2016</a></blockquote>\r\n<p>One user felt the need to reply in a distasteful manner though.</p>\r\n<p>Thuggy-D, a used to be Twitter user, wanted some beef with the fast food chain and not the meat kind. The user&nbsp;resonded to Wendy''s by Tweeting "Your beef is frozen and we all know it. Y''all know we laugh at your slogan ''fresh, never frozen'' right? Like you''re really a joke."</p>\r\n<p>[GOOGLE]</p>\r\n<p>We couldn''t recover the Tweets he sent because he deleted his account. You''ll find the reason why he did soon, for now, here are some screenshots of what he said and how Wendy''s replied.</p>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">if you''re having a bad day today, just remember that you didn''t get dragged by a fast food company on twitter <a href="https://t.co/gUSuHwZLQR">pic.twitter.com/gUSuHwZLQR</a></p>\r\n&mdash; &Gamma;R&Lambda;X@MAGFEST (@Fraxtil) <a href="https://twitter.com/Fraxtil/status/816056124713488384">January 2, 2017</a></blockquote>\r\n<p>After Thuggy-D experienced the humilation set by Wendy''s, he deleted his account. The fast food company then started Tweeting out to everyone who replied negatively about the chain. Here are some cunning replies Wendy''s delivered today:</p>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en"><a href="https://twitter.com/dpeacock980">@dpeacock980</a> Your dignity</p>\r\n&mdash; Wendy''s (@Wendys) <a href="https://twitter.com/Wendys/status/816713888884523008">January 4, 2017</a></blockquote>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en"><a href="https://twitter.com/sophiesphoenix">@sophiesphoenix</a> delete your account</p>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">&mdash; Wendy''s (@Wendys) <a href="https://twitter.com/Wendys/status/816307719087030273">January 3, 2017</a></blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en"><a href="https://twitter.com/LacedlLouie">@LacedlLouie</a> Get one of your 51 followers to roast you.</p>\r\n&mdash; Wendy''s (@Wendys) <a href="https://twitter.com/Wendys/status/816324550703120384">January 3, 2017</a></blockquote>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Wendy''s Twitter account received thousands of engagements as millennials made their way through the fast food company''s many roasts. Will other companies follow Wendy''s creative marketing technique?&nbsp;</p>', 'wendys-brings-its-beef-to-twitter', '', 1, ''),
(9, 'church-of-google.jpg', 'Yes, there is a religion called Googlism and not everyone that&#039;s a Googler can join. In order to join, you must believe that Google is the closest thing to an actual god. They believe that Google has more proof of its divinity than any other traditional god. There are nine proofs that they have listed explaining why Googlism is the mighty religion of today.', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'The Church of Google', 10, 'de169fb0ddfc8973c364e5a34f697cac'),
(10, 'prince-philip-movement.jpg', 'This religious sect is practiced by the Yaohnanen tribe on an island called Tanna in Vanuatu. They believe that the consort of Queen Elizabeth II (Prince Philip), is a divine being. It was said that Prince Philip would return to them and he did. In 1974, Prince Philip and Queen Elizabeth II made an official visit to the island people. This strengthened the beliefs of the Yaohnanen tribe that Prince Philip was indeed their god.', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'Prince Philip Movement', 9, '291279948d6bf4f51ebf4b2d34514cb7'),
(11, 'the-creativity-movement.png', 'If you aren&#039;t Asian, Latino, mixed, black, brown, purple, orange, and any other color other than white, you&#039;re perfect for this! That is, if you&#039;re an atheist of course and racist. Oh, and you&#039;re anti-Semitic and anti-Christian. Then these &quot;Creationists&quot; want you in their &quot;Church.&quot; They are known to plan murders against federal heads. That&#039;s the reason why the Church&#039;s Creator-leader (Matthew F. Hale) got arrested. He was planning to murder a federal judge.', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'The Creativity Movement', 8, '2f68e33d03e5efeb1a1986e2519a97a5'),
(12, 'jediism.jpg', 'Yes, take the -ism out of the word and you have Jedi. This religion was inspired by Star Wars and the people that believe it take it seriously. Light side, dark side, abstract forces, etc - are all ideas Jediists believe in. They combine movie elements and spiritual like beliefs similar to Taoism. If you want to follower their code of conduct, you can read their book called &#039;The 16 Teachings of the Jedi&#039; available online.', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'Jediism', 7, '0488e3da903e0ae89b5ceb7707ed68c0'),
(13, 'church-of-euthanasia.jpg', '&quot;Save the planet, kill yourself!&quot; is basically what the followers of the Church of Euthanasia believe in. They want to reduce the population and they encourage their followers to commit suicide, abortion, and to engage in non-procreative sexual activities only. This group, however, does not support murder. They have one commandment though, &quot;Thou shalt not procreate&quot; - meaning don&#039;t have sex with intentions of having a child.', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'Church Of Euthanasia', 6, 'd37b4d2a6318ac051ef8f09149bf2163'),
(14, 'nation-of-yahweh.jpg', 'Founded in 1979 in Miami, this religion believes that African Americans are the original Israelites. Their main goal is to gather up all African Americans and return them to their original home of Israel. The majority of people who believe in this religion are African Americans. Ever since it&#039;s been founded, the group has faced many accusations of being a black supremacist cult.', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'Nation Of Yahweh', 5, 'aa724029d2cbda97fd1270f509457683'),
(15, 'universe-people.jpg', 'This Czech-Slovak religion is based on Extraterrestrials and alien-like creatures. According to the founder of the religion, aliens orbit Earth continuously and a being named Ashtar watches the people of Earth. Ashtar uses his powers to transport good and loyal followers to another dimension. The aliens that orbit the Earth have fleets of ships. Wonder if NASA saw them yet?', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'Universe People', 4, '9440e621612942aba5a3e0644780a9a6'),
(16, 'vampirism.jpg', 'Thirsty for blood? Just as the name sounds, Vampirism is a religion influenced by several movies, particularly &#039;Dracula&#039; (1897). Followers who practice Vampirism, are placed into two categories: Active and psychic. Active vampires feed on human or animal blood, while psychic vampires indulge on a person&#039;s aurora.', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'Vampirism', 3, '4b742571339a132090ae52476b374dec'),
(17, 'raelism.jpg', 'A French racecar driver by the name of Claude Vorilhons, said that he had been contacted by aliens. The aliens named Claude, Rael. The aliens were really nice to Claude; they even took him to a planet where Jesus, Buddha, Joseph Smith and Confucius were all hanging out. The aliens told Claude that humans were created in an alien lab 25,000 years ago, aliens will be dropping a visit to Jerusalem in 2025, and that Claude is the messenger. They have about 30,000 followers.', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'Raelism', 2, '0ce628608145f29d128299e68ba48393'),
(18, 'happy-science.jpg', 'Founded in Japan, this religion&#039;s main goal is to make everyone happy. Ryuho Okawa, the founder, believes that he is a god and his followers believe it. This religion was founded in 1986 and they also believe that North Korea and China are planning to attack Japan with their nuclear weapons. So if you want others to be happy and follow their same beliefs, then you might as well be a follower of Happy Science!', 'extremely-weird-religions', 'Happy Science', 1, '15bcd49f006fa93db0f79bc1fcac99e7'),
