(56, '3d-printer.jpg', 'This is not a joke. You can also print 3D printers with another 3D printer. The RepRap is an open source 3D printer that does that easily. You can just program the printer to do what you want it to do, and bam. You have yourself another 3D printer.', 'ten-crazy-3d-printed-things', '3D Printers', 3, '74bc6d57f5033b42bd1352254eb766a0'),
(57, '3d-printed-bicycle.jpg', 'Imagine a 3D printed bicycle in your garage. With the use of the 3D printer, you can build it. Show it off to your neighbor, because wellâ€¦thatâ€™s the only good thing itâ€™s for.', 'ten-crazy-3d-printed-things', 'Bicycles', 2, '727bdfd4472d8a9bd3080509931e31d4'),
(58, '3d-printed-iphone-case.jpg', 'Struggling to find the iPhone case just for you? Well look no more! With the 3D printer technology, you can actually make the case yourself. Designed and created by you. The best part? You donâ€™t even have to wait for it to ship from China!', 'ten-crazy-3d-printed-things', 'iPhone Cases', 1, '5222090728ee62686a8965d574e37a40'),
(64, 'siri-pronounce-name.jpg', 'When Siri mispronounces a word, simply say â€œThatâ€™s not how you pronounce â€œ[Word]â€ and then the alternate options will be given to you. These options will let you teach Siri how to pronounce that specific word.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Teach Siri How To Talk', 11, '984a78322a7bebb5ff8611000c4103ae'),
(65, 'swipe-right.jpg', 'Want to go back on a page, but too lazy to press that button? Just swipe your finger from the left to the right of the screen, and watch the magic unfold.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Built In Back Button', 10, '5fe4ab493447a4ff28d1e6da831a3b89'),
(66, 'Near-Me-640x568.jpg', 'Thereâ€™s an option at the bottom of the App store called â€œNear Me.â€ This option will show you the most popular apps people in your area have downloaded.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Popular Apps Near You', 9, '166b97931b38767993b4981ea6d72bd1'),
(67, 'close-iphone-apps.jpg', 'You can actually close multiple apps at once. Just swipe up with two or three fingers.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Close More Than One App', 8, 'a501fb3b96eca252f80743a9f519ceb7'),
(68, 'block-contact-calls-messages-iphone.jpg', 'You donâ€™t need to download an app to block that number. You can simply open the spammer conversationalist and tap â€œDetailsâ€ in the top right corner. Afterwards, tap the â€œiâ€ next to the phone number and select block this caller.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Block Numbers', 7, '51609ff518ae4c8147c8882d56af83ea'),
(69, 'siri-voice.jpg', 'Tired of the voice of Siri? You can easily change it by going to settings, general, Siri and then scroll down to â€œVoice Gender.â€ Here, you can give Siri either a male voice or a female voice.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Change Siriâ€™s Gender', 6, '092795815de9310db10141d2dca01516'),
(70, 'siri-relationships.jpg', 'Tell Siri your relationships, and itâ€™ll remember them. For example, if you have a contact named Matthew, just tell it â€œMatthew is my brotherâ€ and itâ€™ll remember it.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Siri Can Make Connections', 5, '11289e31015e52cd2f97956d6ce0db0e'),
(71, 'iphone-location.jpg', 'Your iPhone is built to track every location youâ€™ve been to. Creepy huh? Just go to settings, privacy, location services, system services, and then check out the â€œfrequent locationsâ€ option.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'It Tracks Every Location', 4, '9eeb05806837d57bcb2749eeda1a5710'),
(72, 'iphone-undo-mistake.jpg', 'Applied the wrong filter or made a typo? Well you can easily undo any of your mistakes by simply shaking your device.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Undo Your Mistake', 3, 'c145a8f1fc59fc0e721ca9eb3f2e869d'),
(73, 'siri-flight-information.jpg', 'Siri can help you find airplanes flying above you. Just ask â€œWhat airplanes are flying over [your location] right now?â€', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'Siriâ€™s Airplane Finder', 2, '6093f6a10aec45418b8c4c2421598fc5'),
(74, 'ipad-charger.jpg', 'How you may ask? Simple. If you have an iPad charger, then charge your iPhone with it. The iPhone charger is rated at 5W, however, the iPad charger is rated at 12W.', '11-incredible-things-your-iphone-can-do', 'You Can Charge It Faster', 1, 'a7cb55c590ec921093183860c5a24d69'),
(75, '', '<h1 class="sub-title" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #666699;"><em><img src="http://whateven.com/stories/media/images/sleep-deprived.jpg" alt="Sleep deprived" width="850" height="456" /></em></span></h1>\r\n<h1 class="sub-title" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #666699;"><em>Meet Charlie</em></span></h1>\r\n<p>After an 8 hour sleep, we feel refreshed, energized and ready to perform everyday tasks. Our body is working at peak levels and our day begins, but what if we just stopped sleeping after that? What if instead of sleeping, we forced ourselves to stay awake? Is it something we should do? Certainly not.<br /><br />Charlie is confident to do so. Who&rsquo;s Charlie? Well Charlie is just an imaginary person we just made up. What he&rsquo;ll go through isn&rsquo;t though.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://whateven.com/stories/media/images/new-day.jpg" alt="Sun rise" width="850" height="638" /></p>\r\n<h1 class="sub-title" style="text-align: center;"><em><span style="color: #666699;">The Start Of The Day</span></em></h1>\r\n<p>Charlie&rsquo;s day starts with a cup of coffee and a sandwich. The cup of coffee gives Charlie the boost to combat the day&rsquo;s workload. An ordinary day to most people, but today Charlie&rsquo;s coffee crash isn&rsquo;t an ordinary crash. He&rsquo;ll have to fight it because he can&rsquo;t sleep.<br /><br />Already 5 hours in the day, and Charlie is feeling a bit tired. He can still work, but an afternoon nap sounds pretty nice right now. Charlie is not really mad that he can&rsquo;t nap. Why? Well after his 8 hour sleep, Charlie produced dopamine.<br /><br />Dopamine is a chemical produced by the brain that in return causes positivity and will make a person happier. Dopamine is produced by everyone after a goodnight&rsquo;s sleep. Charlie knows he can combat the day a little further, but not for long.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://whateven.com/stories/media/images/lego-recollection.jpg" alt="Lego trashman" width="850" height="568" /></p>\r\n<h1 class="sub-title" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #666699;"><em>Recollection Mode</em></span></h1>\r\n<p>After 11 hours of no sleep, Charlie&rsquo;s brain begins to sort all the memories he experienced over the course of the day. This recollection mode uses a good amount of energy and will eventually make Charlie&rsquo;s muscles weak and limp. The muscles in his eyelids, legs, and arms will all become drained of energy. This is the initial sign of Charlie&rsquo;s body saying it&rsquo;s time to sleep!<br /><br />Fourteen hours in, and Charlie&rsquo;s brain wants him to turn off the lights. Headaches start to emerge and his eyes look kind of red. The only way to solve this problem is to go to sleep, but let&rsquo;s take Charlie a bit further with 20 hours of no sleep.</p>\r\n<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="http://whateven.com/stories/media/images/fried-brain.jpg" /></p>\r\n<h1 class="sub-title" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #666699;"><em>Fried Brain</em></span></h1>\r\n<p>At this point, Charlie&rsquo;s brain can&rsquo;t properly sort the day&rsquo;s events because it&rsquo;s too busy powering his alertness. His body begins to go into protection mode. Headaches start to worsen and Charlie&rsquo;s a mess! After 24 hours of no sleep, it starts to get dangerous. Charlie&rsquo;s reaction time begins to slow down and he also begins to lose his sense of coordination.<br /><br />He limps around begging us to let him sleep, but our imaginary friend needs to stay in a little longer for this article. He tries to fight us, but he can&rsquo;t accurately hit us. He swings and instead hits our small green plant. Charlie trips on his legs, and there you have it. An embarrassing look at how 20 hours of no sleep can look like.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://whateven.com/stories/media/images/hallucinations.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="473" /></p>\r\n<h1 class="sub-title" style="text-align: center;"><em><span style="color: #666699;">You Start To Hallucinate</span></em></h1>\r\n<p>Two days pass, and now Charlie is exhausted. Mentally he&rsquo;s going crazy, physically he can&rsquo;t move without falling down, and his immune system is also beginning to shut down.<br /><br />With Charlie&rsquo;s immune system shut down, he is now vulnerable to any threat. He is now losing control of his arms and legs and his brain is deprived of energy. He may eat a ton of food, but if he doesn&rsquo;t sleep the food is useless.<br /><br />Day three begins and Charlie is starting to act crazy. He&rsquo;s starting to hallucinate and jump around. He is so deprived of energy that his tongue ceases to move. This isn&rsquo;t coincidence though. The brain needs to cut off communication with this muscle in order to slow down the energy consumption.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://whateven.com/stories/media/images/ugly-dog.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="573" /></p>\r\n<h1 class="sub-title" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #666699;"><em>Ugly Duckling</em></span></h1>\r\n<p>It is now the fourth day, and Charlie is looking horrible. His appearance is declining and his health isn&rsquo;t looking too good. At this point, Charlie is too worn out to do anything. He lays in bed, however, he can&rsquo;t sense anything. He is unable to function anymore.<br /><br />Lucky for Charlie, he went to sleep and woke up after 10 hours fine! Sleep deprivation does not do any damage to your body, but it does do some damage at the moment.<br /><br />After some days without sleep, you can go to sleep and feel normal afterwards. The longest time a person has gone with no sleep is 11 days, but that doesn&rsquo;t mean you can do it too. A Chinese man tried it and died. Lucky for Charlie, he&rsquo;s awake and ready to start his day.</p>', 'what-if-you-stopped-sleeping', '', 1, ''),
(76, 'sunset.jpg', 'If the Earth slowed down to one rotation a year, a condition called &#039;sun synchronous,&#039; then one day would last 365 days long. The day would be 6 months long of scorching sun and 6 months long of freezing night. If the Earth stopped spinning altogether, then your region would indicate what you have permanently. So if you stopped in nighttime, then you&#039;ll be stuck in the twilight zone forever.', 'what-if-the-earth-stopped-spinning', 'A 133,225 Day Year', 5, '122b77d0ae15d9c40f0e743fe8463bee'),
(77, 'french-grenade-catapult.jpg', 'If the Earth stopped spinning suddenly right now, then you&#039;d be catapulted sideways at unreal speeds. The Earth right now is moving at 67,000 MPH, so with the laws of physics every human, animal, object would be flown across. With such high speeds, trees and plants would be burnt to death. Thus, this alone with the fact that plants are all gone, would mean the end.', 'what-if-the-earth-stopped-spinning', 'Supersonic Trajectory', 4, '96cb19305660b6d482290aa4fe154b89'),
(78, 'high-waves.jpg', 'The sudden stoppage of Earth would blow away every mass of water. This would cause giant tsunamis engulfing every land mass. Your only chances of survival would be living somewhere away from water. When we say away, we mean AWAY. Far, far, far away. These tsunamis aren&#039;t normal. So not normal that we&#039;re coining the term Gunamis - Giant tsunamis.', 'what-if-the-earth-stopped-spinning', 'Surf&#039;s Up!', 3, 'a07a0d03b4009589db76aad9228c49b3'),
(79, 'earth.jpg', 'The Earth would become curvy. So curvy that it&#039;ll become a perfect sphere! Due to the stoppage force though, the curvy Earth would be on fire, literally! We&#039;re not talking about it being sexy Venus, so don&#039;t get your hopes up. Earth is still too hot for you.', 'what-if-the-earth-stopped-spinning', 'Earth Will Get Curvy', 2, '1ac1d5ef1e23fcb71425ca708d188145'),
(80, 'international-space-station.jpg', 'Yes. Lucky for us, it won&#039;t happen in our lifetime...unless some big asteroid comes and stops it. Earth is slowing down and that&#039;s a fact! We have shorter days than we did 10 years ago, but it&#039;s only by some milliseconds or seconds. It&#039;ll stop in a billion years or so, but once it does it&#039;ll destroy everything. Keep it cool planet Earth, keep it cool.', 'what-if-the-earth-stopped-spinning', 'Will Earth Stop Spinning?', 1, '4a778268abdbbe66321971ac4526c3e2');
