(226, '', '<p dir="ltr" lang="en" style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/-JdcoH9deic" width="560" height="314"></iframe>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ever since last year''s coffee cup disaster, Starbucks has been trying to make it feel a <strong><em>latte</em> </strong>like Christmas. That''s because it''s giving out free tall espresso drinks nationwide through January 2<sup>nd&nbsp;</sup></p>\r\n<p>Here''s one disclaimer though, if you want to drink at the coffee giant, then you should go between the hours of 1 to 2 p.m because that is when they''ll serve you free espressos.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../../stories/media/images/starbucks-christmas58604b8999234.png" alt="Starbucks Christmas Cup" width="850" height="567" border="0" /></p>\r\n<h6 style="text-align: left;">People.com&nbsp;&copy; All rights reserved</h6>\r\n<p>If you''re a Starbucks lover, then you can go to <a title="Starbucks Cheer" href="http://starbucks.com/cheer" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">starbucks.com/cheer</a>&nbsp;to see if your location supports this offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You can also receive a Starbucks <em>"Cheer Card"&nbsp;</em>at your participating local Starbucks which will provide discounts on beverages, sandwiches, or a free cookie when you purchase a drink.</p>', 'starbucks-is-giving-out-free-coffee-10-days', '', 1, ''),
