(243, '', '<h1>Introduction</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Web hosting</strong> can be expensive, but it really doesn''t <em>have to be</em>. If you''re still not on your feet, then it would be best to get <strong><em>cheap</em></strong> web hosting for your blog or business.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are many types of hosting. Top notch hosting is <strong>VPS hosting</strong> which stands for ''Virtual Private Servers.'' With VPS hosting, your site resides on a private server. Only get this if if you are pretty big, but for the rest of us shared web hosting is what we need.</p>\r\n<p>Over the years, <strong>web hosting</strong> prices have declined and the extras they provide have increased. Web hosting companies are trying their best to let you sign up to their plans. We''ve filtered this list to show you only the <strong>best and cheapest web hosting</strong> companies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;[GOOGLE]</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">10. Web Hosting Hub: $3.99/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="Web Hosting Hub" href="http://www.webhostinghub.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/web-hosting-hub.png" alt="Web Hosting Hub" width="850" height="420" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="3.8" min="0" max="5">3.8 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>3.8/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>Web hosting hub is very new web hosting company. It all started back in 2010 and they have rocketed since. They offer an adequate amount of offers as a new web host. With a free domain and $75 advertising credits, Web Hosting Hub is a great cheap web hosting company!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited bandwidth, disk space, and email accounts.</li>\r\n<li>Free domain, website builder, and eCommerce tools.</li>\r\n<li>$75 advertising credits.</li>\r\n<li>Hosting placed on SSD (solid state drive) for faster site retrieval.</li>\r\n<li>24/7 support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Only 2 domains allowed.</li>\r\n<li>No community support forum.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;[GOOGLE]</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">9. GoDaddy: $3.99/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="GoDaddy.com" href="http://www.GoDaddy.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/godaddy-web-hosting.png" alt="GoDaddy Web Hosting" width="850" height="420" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.0" min="0" max="5">4.0 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.0/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>It''s the most famous web hosting company in the world. It''s built on speed, performance, and great customer support. For only $3.99/month, you''ll get a partner in your business that actually cares. The downside of GoDaddy though, is that their disk space is very limited for this plan.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited bandwidth.</li>\r\n<li>10 MySQL databases.</li>\r\n<li>Free domain.</li>\r\n<li>25 subdomains.</li>\r\n<li>Great 24/7 support.</li>\r\n<li>Always has advertising coupons.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Only single domain allowed on hosting.</li>\r\n<li>Only 100GB disk space.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">8. HostGator: $3.95/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="HostGator" href="http://www.hostgator.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/hostgator-web-hosting.png" alt="Hostgator web hosting" width="850" height="420" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.1" min="0" max="5">4.1 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.1/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>HostGator is a classic cheap web host with great free features. Small businesses will love the interface and free advertising credits included in the package. It is interesting to point out that if you upgrade to the business package you will get a free toll number for your business. Awesome right?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited bandwidth, sub domains, MySQL databases, email accounts, and disk space.</li>\r\n<li>eCommerce included.</li>\r\n<li>Website statistics.</li>\r\n<li>4,500 website templates.</li>\r\n<li>99% uptime.</li>\r\n<li>Google and Bing $100 advertising credits.</li>\r\n<li>24/7 Support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>No free domain.</li>\r\n<li>Only single domain allowed on the hosting.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;[GOOGLE]</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">7. Bluehost: $3.49/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="BlueHost" href="http://www.bluehost.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/bluehost-web-hosting.png" alt="Bluehost Web Hosting" width="850" height="420" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.1" min="0" max="5">4.1 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.1/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bluehost is a well known web hosting company. It offers great performance and reliability with great support. The downside to Bluehost is that more money does make a difference. They think if you really are serious about your business, then paying an extra $2 per month for their plus package shouldn''t be a problem. The upside to Bluehost is that it does come with unlimited bandwidth and a free domain.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited bandwidth.</li>\r\n<li>Free domain and site builders.</li>\r\n<li>24/7 Support.</li>\r\n<li>Great uptime.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>50GB Website space.</li>\r\n<li>Only 1 website is allowed.</li>\r\n<li>Only 5 email accounts.</li>\r\n<li>Limited email space.</li>\r\n<li>No advertising credits.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">6. InMotion: $2.95/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="InMotion" href="http://www.inmotionhosting.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/inmotion-web-hosting.png" alt="inmotion-web-hosting" width="850" height="420" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.0" min="0" max="5">4.0 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.0/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>The price may seem cheap, but it does have some major flaws if you are a small business owner. If you''re looking to sell online, the basic (Launch) package,&nbsp;is not eCommerce ready. That means you cannot sell any products online. You can, however, build your own system. Building your own system requires some programming knowledge though, so if you are not looking to hire someone you should choose their top selling package (Power).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited disk space, email and monthly transfers.</li>\r\n<li>Free website builder and domain.</li>\r\n<li>$250 in advertising credits.</li>\r\n<li>Hosting placed on SSD (solid state drive) for faster site retrieval.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Not eCommerce ready.</li>\r\n<li>Only 2 MySQL databases.</li>\r\n<li>Only 2 domains allowed on account.</li>\r\n<li>Must purchase more expensive package for better support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;[GOOGLE]</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">5. Fat Cow Hosting: $3.15/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="Fat Cow Web Hosting" href="http://www.fatcow.com/fatcow/special-promo.bml?LinkName=AB1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/fat-cow-web-hosting.png" alt="Fat Cow Web Hosting" width="850" height="420" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.2" min="0" max="5">4.2 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.2/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>It''s cheap web hosting with a silly name. Even the website is shaped like the back of the milk carton. Below the fun is a reliable web host. With extra features, like a free website builder and a shopping cart, Fat Cow really knows how to treat your buck.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited disk space, domains, MySQL databases and POP mailboxes.</li>\r\n<li>Free domain name, website builder, shopping cart, and script barn.</li>\r\n<li>Google and Bing $100 advertising credits.</li>\r\n<li>24/7 Support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Will have to pay regular price after introductory period is over.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">4. Idea Host: $2.99/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="ideahost" href="http://www.ideahost.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/Idea-Host-web-host.jpg" alt="Idea Host" width="820" height="346" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.2" min="0" max="5">4.2 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.2/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>Idea Host is not recommended for big businesses. As a domain host for small businesses, they are exceptional. They offer the same package most host providers provide, but their difference is that you get a free domain name. They''re relatively new, but that doesn''t make them adequate web hosts.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited disk space, bandwidth, MySQL databases, FTP accounts, and domains.</li>\r\n<li>Free email address.</li>\r\n<li>Free domain name.</li>\r\n<li>Google and Bing $100 advertising credits.</li>\r\n<li>24/7 Support.</li>\r\n<li>1000s of free templates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Relatively new to the industry.</li>\r\n<li>User community small.</li>\r\n<li>Not 100% up time.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;[GOOGLE]</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">3. HostClear: $2.99/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="HostClear" href="http://www.hostclear.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/hostClear-web-hosting.png" alt="HostClear Web Hosting" width="850" height="433" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.5" min="0" max="5">4.5 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.5/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you''re looking for something quick and easy, then HostClear is for you. Create a site easily with 1000s of templates using their free site builder. HostClear is the perfect solution for small business owners that don''t know how to code and want to get up and running in minutes.</p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Pros:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited disk space, bandwidth, domains, SQL databases and email accounts.</li>\r\n<li>Free site builder.</li>\r\n<li>Free domain name.</li>\r\n<li>Google and Bing $100 advertising credits.</li>\r\n<li>24/7 Support.</li>\r\n<li>1000s of free templates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong><span style="color: #000000;">Cons:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lacks email aliases.</li>\r\n<li>Lacks mail scripts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">2. eHost: $2.75/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="eHost" href="http://www.ehost.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/ehost-web-hosting.jpg" alt="eHost Web Hosting" width="850" height="385" /></a><span style="color: #ffffff;"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.5" min="0" max="5">4.5 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.5/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>eHost is a remarkable free web and domain hosting service that combines simplicity with cost. The only&nbsp;major disadvantage we found with this web hosting service is that they do not have a VPS plan. That means if you ever outgrow eHosting, you must switch over to another web host.</p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Pros:</strong><br /></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited disk space, bandwidth, and domains.</li>\r\n<li>Free domain registration.</li>\r\n<li>Free site builder.</li>\r\n<li>Google and Bing $100 advertising credits.</li>\r\n<li>24/7 Support.</li>\r\n<li>Online store.</li>\r\n<li>Site analytics software.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Does not contain VPS hosting.</li>\r\n<li>Renewal cost is higher.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;[GOOGLE]</p>\r\n<h2><span style="background-color: #333333; color: #ffffff;">1. iPage: $1.99/mo.</span></h2>\r\n<p><a title="iPage" href="http://www.ipage.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="../../stories/media/images/ipage-web-hosting-min.jpg" alt="iPage Web Hosting" width="977" height="610" /></a></p>\r\n<p><meter value="4.7" min="0" max="5">4.7 out of 5</meter>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: terminal, monaco, monospace;"><strong>4.7/5</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong></p>\r\n<p>One of the <em><strong>cheapest web hosting</strong></em> available, iPage brilliantly gives you some experience before you take out your wallet. For over a decade, iPage has been providing great deals for hosting and it continues to bring wonders to small business owners. With free search engine marketing credits, it is no wonder why iPage is #1.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlimited disk space, domains, MySQL databases, and email addresses.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Unlimited bandwidth.*</li>\r\n<li>Free eCommerce hosting.</li>\r\n<li>Google and Bing $100 advertising credits.</li>\r\n<li>24/7 Support.</li>\r\n<li>Web statistics.</li>\r\n<li>Site security.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>After a few months, you will be priced regularly.</li>\r\n<li>No community forum.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>Conclusion</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Great and cheap web hosting</strong> is hard to find. Even though these companies offer a lot, most of them will raise their prices after their introductory phase. It is highly recommended that you test these web hosts before you actually consider buying their premium packages.</p>\r\n<p>As a small business owner, you should consider carefully before purchasing any of these web hosting packages. If you have a problem, your business can''t afford shutting down their website for web host maintenance.</p>\r\n<p>If you are a small site owner and not a small business, then you are recommended to buy something cheap to try before you actually purchase a package.</p>\r\n<p>[GOOGLE]</p>', 'cheap-web-hosting', '', 1, '');
